opilot Workspace is an **AI-powered cloud development environment** that offers:\n- **\"From Issue to PR\" automation**: Users select an Issue, and the AI automatically analyzes, plans, generates code, and creates a Pull Request\n- **Deep GitHub integration**: Tight integration with GitHub's collaborative features\n- **Multi-file editing**: Capable of handling complex code changes across multiple files\n- **Agent-based autonomous execution**: AI agents can independently execute coding tasks\n\n### Pricing\n- Requires a GitHub Copilot subscription ($10-39/month)\n- Included as part of the Copilot subscription service\n\n### Recent Developments (2025)\nThe search results show significant GitHub Copilot developments in 2025, including:\n- **February 2025**: GitHub announced major updates to Copilot\n- **Visual capabilities**: Copilot introduced image-to-code functionality\n- **Copilot Spaces**: New feature supporting issues and pull requests as context (in public preview as of June 2025)\n\n### Limitations\n- The search results **do not confirm** a specific February 2026 launch date\n- Most references point to earlier availability (2024-2025 timeframe)\n- Information about a February 2026 launch may be uncertain or not officially announced yet\n\n**Recommendation**: For the most accurate and up-to-date information about Copilot Workspace availability and any future launch dates, I'd recommend checking GitHub's official blog or announcements directly at github.com or during GitHub Universe events.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
